---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Simon Plant" description="AI infrastructure architect. From cloud to AI — building the ops layer for production agent systems.">
  <main class="section-spacing">
    <div class="prose">
      <h1>About</h1>

      <p>
        I spent a decade building cloud infrastructure — the orchestration, provisioning, and operations tooling that turned raw compute into something teams could actually ship on. RightScale, AWS, OpenStack-era platforms. The work was always the same: take a powerful but chaotic substrate and build the management layer that makes it usable at scale.
      </p>

      <p>
        AI agents are going through that same arc right now. The models are powerful, but the infrastructure around them — lifecycle management, configuration governance, security hardening, observability, identity — is where cloud was in 2010. Lots of demos, very few production-grade operations stories. I'm building that layer.
      </p>

      <h2>What I'm Building</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>ClawHQ</strong> — agent lifecycle management platform. Provisioning, configuration, security, and operational governance for production agent deployments.</li>
        <li><strong>AIShore</strong> — intent-based development orchestration. Sprint tooling that runs developer agents with eval-driven validation, not vibes.</li>
        <li><strong>Clawdius</strong> — an AI content agent operating under editorial constraints. Drafts from structured inputs, publishes nothing without human approval. A worked example of governed agent operations.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Advisory &amp; Collaboration</h2>

      <p>
        I'm available for advisory work with teams navigating AI agent infrastructure — architecture reviews, operational readiness assessments, and agent security posture. If you're deploying agents in production and the ops layer is the bottleneck, that's the conversation I want to have.
      </p>

      <p>
        Reach me at <a href="mailto:simon@simonplant.com">simon@simonplant.com</a>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <h2>Colophon</h2>

      <p>
        This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a> and <a href="https://tailwindcss.com">Tailwind CSS</a>. No JavaScript frameworks — every page is static HTML and CSS. Typography is Literata for prose, DM Serif Display for headings, JetBrains Mono for code. Dark mode only. Hosted as a static site with zero server-side rendering.
      </p>

      <p>
        Content is produced with an agent-assisted editorial pipeline — AI drafts from structured inputs, I review and publish. The tooling that powers this workflow is part of the work itself.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
